The 10-year-old autistic boy was locked in a metal cage at a Canberra school . 
  The cage was specifically designed as a 'withdrawal space' for the boy . 
  The principal of the school has been suspended and an investigation into the incident is underway . 
  The structure was in place from March 10 to March 27 . 
  ACT Education Minister Joy Burch said it is a horrifying situation . 
 